name: Panucho | Soft and Crispy Taco
description: Panucho is a traditional dish of Yucatecan gastronomy. It consists of a corn tortilla fried in oil or butter filled with beans, so that it is slightly puffed and soft, served with lettuce, tomato, tanned onion, shredded turkey or chicken and avocado. There is also the version without beans called Salbut. Like all Yucatecan food, it is usually accompanied by chopped habanero pepper.
